    "Figure 6.6Figure 6.",
    "Real-world experiments with predicted 3D traces.",
    "We evaluate TraceGen and baselines on four real-world manipulation tasks on a Franka Research 3 robot, showing that the predicted 3D traces transfer effectively to real-robot execution.",
    "Our experiments address three questions: (1) Effectiveness of TraceGen: Does planning in compact 3D trace space improve performance and inference efficiency compared to pixel-based alternatives?",
    "5.1) (2) Human-Robot Transfer: Can TraceGen enable efficient human-to-robot transfer from uncalibrated, in-the-wild videos with differing camera, backgrounds, and object layouts?"
